trend_summary: Built-up footprint grows steadily, mainly around the airport in the northeast and the town core, while most western hills stay wooded. New highways and interchanges knit districts together, residential infill fills former clearings, and a reservoir enlarges, adding blue space. Overall fabric remains green-buffered, giving a medium-density suburban character.
notable_changes: Progressive expansion of the airport/apron area in the northeast with additional paved surfaces.
Central reservoir enlarged and darkens, replacing previous woodland patches.
New highway segment and cloverleaf interchange built along the northern arc, improving connectivity.
Residential infill and estate growth south and east of the town core, shrinking scattered forest gaps.
Light industrial/commercial blocks added near major junctions, increasing impervious surface coverage.
